    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractRequest

        public AbstractRequest(HttpMethod method,
               String url,
               Map<String,String> requestHeaders,
               Map<String,String> queryParams)
        Create a new AbstractRequest.

        Note that there are some representation invariants for the AbstractRequest object. For example, a HttpMethod.GET cannot contain a body.

        Parameters:
        method - the HttpMethod of the request type.
        url - the URL to request (and to append query string parameters to).
        requestHeaders - the headers to add to the request. This cannot contain null keys or null values.
        queryParams - the query string parameters. This cannot contain null keys or null values.

      • AbstractRequest

        public AbstractRequest(HttpMethod method,
               Uri url,
               Map<String,String> requestHeaders)
                throws IllegalArgumentException
        Create a new AbstractRequest from an absolute URL.
        Parameters:
        method - the HttpMethod of the request type.
        url - The URL to request. This can include query parameters.
        requestHeaders - the headers to add to the request. This cannot contain null keys or null values.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the URI passed in isn't an absolute URL.
